        public static final int MAX_RECORD_LENGTH

    • Method Detail

      • useBackOffRetryStrategy

        public boolean useBackOffRetryStrategy()
        Returns:
        A value indicating whether to use a back-off (exponenential) in case of individual block failures. If set to 'false' every retry is handled immediately; otherwise an amount of time is waited between retries, as a function of power of 2.

      • setUseBackOffRetryStrategy

        public void setUseBackOffRetryStrategy(boolean isEnabled)
        Parameters:
        isEnabled - A value indicating whether to use a back-off (exponenential) in case of individual block failures. If set to 'false' every retry is handled immediately; otherwise an amount of time is waited between retries, as a function of power of 2.

      • upload

        public void upload()
            throws Exception
        Uploads the portion of the InputFilePath to the given TargetStreamPath, starting at the given StartOffset. The segment is further divided into equally-sized blocks which are uploaded in sequence. Each such block is attempted a certain number of times; if after that it still cannot be uploaded, the entire segment is aborted (in which case no cleanup is performed on the server).
        Throws:
        Exception - if there is any failure during the upload

      • waitForRetry

        public static void waitForRetry(int attemptCount,
                                boolean useBackOffRetryStrategy)
                         throws InterruptedException
        Enables use of a back off retry strategy, allowing a caller to wait before attempting an action again.
        Parameters:
        attemptCount - The number of attempts that have already been done
        useBackOffRetryStrategy - whether to use the back off strategy or not.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - Thrown if there is an interrupt during the sleep.
